  1. MNIST now sourced at runtime: _baixar_e_preparar_mnist() downloads from
     Google CVDF storage (~12 MB gz files cached in assets/_mnist_raw/) and
     creates the balanced 4000+1000 subset. No committed file needed.
  2. All sandbox states (initial/collapsed/final) and encoder checkpoints
     (epoch0/early/late/16d_late) use "generate if absent" pattern:
       if PRETRAINED and file.exists(): load
       else: compute inline + save to assets/
